    <div class=3D"text-section-body"><h2>When Do ACT Scores Come Out?&nbsp;=
</h2>
<p>The initial score release table provides the date when scores start beco=
ming available. The initial release of scores includes any test (paper or o=
nline) that has been received, processed, passed all validation checks, and=
 are not impacted by an irregularity.&nbsp;</p>
<p>You=E2=80=99ll see your scores as soon as they become available, but if =
you take the optional writing test, your scores won=E2=80=99t be reported u=
ntil all scores from your test date are released.</p>
<p>Scores continue to be processed regularly during business hours, so if y=
our scores were part of the initial release, we'll continuously release sco=
res as they become available.</p>
<p><b>See the chart for initial score release dates.&nbsp;</b></p>
</div>
