    <h3>
     =20
       Can I Request a Copy of My ACT Questions and Answers?&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
    </h3>

   =20

    <div class=3D"text-section-body"><p>Certain national test dates and cen=
ters give you the opportunity to order a copy of your questions, your answe=
rs, the answer key, and scoring instructions=E2=80=94plus the writing promp=
t, scoring rubric, and scores assigned to the optional writing test.&nbsp;<=
/p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;"><a href=3D"https://www.act.org/content/ac=
t/en/products-and-services/the-act/scores/request-a-copy-of-qa.html"><b>Req=
uest ACT My Answer Key</b></a></p>
<h3>How Can I Find an Old ACT Score?</h3>
<p>If you tested before September 2011, you scores will not be available in=
 <a href=3D"https://my.act.org/account/signin?location=3Dhttps://my.act.org=
">MyACT</a>. <a href=3D"https://www.act.org/content/act/en/contact-act.html=
">Contact ACT</a> to request scores.</p>
<h3>Can ACT Test Scores Be Cancelled?</h3>
<p>ACT reserves the right to cancel test scores when there is reason to bel=
ieve the scores are invalid. See the <a href=3D"https://www.act.org/content=
/dam/act/secured/documents/Terms-and-Conditions.pdf" target=3D"_blank">ACT =
Terms and Conditions (PDF)</a> for details.</p>
<p>Outside of State testing and District testing, you may request to cancel=
 scores for a particular test date. <a href=3D"https://www.act.org/content/=
act/en/products-and-services/the-act/the-act-test-contact-us.html">Contact =
us online</a> and we will provide you a form to complete and return to us. =
We will then permanently cancel that score record for the indicated test da=
te and send cancellation notices to any score recipients.</p>
<h3>Can I Change a Score Recipient?&nbsp;</h3>
<p>If you need to change a score recipient, you have until Thursday, 12 pm =
CT after the regularly scheduled test date.</p>
